In article <linux.kernel.19990512094644.B8219@helium.inexs.com>,
Chuck Campbell  <campbell@neosoft.com> wrote:
>I'm picking up a machine this afternoon, and it comes with a DVD drive.
>
>My understanding is that there are no drivers for these as of yet.
    The normal IDE device driver treats a DVD drive like an IDE drive.
    I've got a K5/166 machine that I put a Hitachi/IBM DVD drive into,
    and it works just fine for installing Mastodon Linux from CD. I'd
    suspect that the RH CD installer would work just as well.
